A taxi burst into flames in Umtentweni, recently after colliding with a car and leaving 10 people injured. Netcare 911 responded to the collision on the Old St Faith’s Road and found that a taxi and car were involved in the crash resulting in the taxi bursting into flames. Shawn Herbst, Netcare 911 spokesperson, said: “A total of 10 occupants sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. The patients were treated on scene and once stabilised were transported by various ambulance services to hospital for further treatment.”